BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260514T171735Z
UID:SC-401FC7BB-5C00-46A4-B907-37B743342664
DTSTART:20260514T130000
DTEND:20260514T133000
SUMMARY:S: Exit interview (S. Birnbaum)\, solo [@exit]
CATEGORIES:@exit,AssocDH
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VTODO
UID:TODO-401FC7BB-5C00-46A4-B907-37B743342664
DTSTAMP:20260514T171735Z
SUMMARY:Exit interview (S. Birnbaum)\, solo [@exit]
DESCRIPTION:• 1. What is your general impression of your experience in PSE?
 \n  • Enjoy\, positive impression\, learned a lot.  Department does a\n   
  good job representing itself before students arrive.  GEO\n    benefits.\
 n• 2. What did you like or dislike about curriculum and comprehensive\n  e
 xam process?\n  • Cumes: hard but seems pros and cons.  Cumes overshadowed
 \n    coursework in Spring because of preparation.\n  • Curriculum: overal
 l classes have great breadth.  Labs were very\n    useful but sometimes se
 emed chemistry was unprepared\;\n    characterization labs.  ST courses: g
 reat when aligned with\n    research topic\; better if announced earlier.\
 n• 3. What is the greatest strength of the PSE program?\n  • Appreciates e
 ffort by faculty to be collaborative with\n    department\, University\, a
 nd beyond.\n• 4. What is the greatest weakness or need for improvement of 
 the\n  PSE program?\n\n• 5. What are your next steps?
CATEGORIES:@exit,AssocDH
SEQUENCE:1
PRIORITY:5
STATUS:NEEDS-ACTION
END:VTODO
